723094f-a.text: St. Catherines Park: Children playing in the undeveloped playground prior to its later formal arrangement. This site utilizes the west frontage of First Avenue from E. 67th to 68th Street's. Upon the latter appears the German Reformed Protestant N. Church (translation of the inscription over the west door). Bromleys Map of 1922 gives this organization as the German Evang. Reformed Church. The parsonage at the right bears No. 355 East 68th Street.

707647f-a.text:
First Ave., at the S.E. corner of East 67th Street. Also shown is East 67th Street, south side, east from First to and including York Aves. The view shows the Bethany Memorial Church, occupying the corner site, with the
nursery (402 East 67th Street), adjoining it.
September 15, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.

707650f-b.text:
First Avenue, east side, from East 67th to 68th Streets, showing the New York Trade School occupying this avenue frontage. This structure was rased about 1932 and the new Memorial Hospital for the Treatment of Cancer and Allied Diseases erected during 1939. View 2 is an eastward view of the new building. This extends to York Avenue, beyond which appear the buildin. s of the Rockefeller
Institute for Medical Research.
Note the bus on 68th Street slightly east of First Avenue.
View 1: Septmmber 7, 1927
View 2: April 10, 1940
P. L. Sperr

707649f.text:
First Avenue, at the S. E. corner of East 67th Street showing the Bethany Memorial Church and its
5 story nursery (No. 402 E.).
This is given in the City Record Supplement as being owned by the Madison Avenue Reformed Church. To the right appears a portion of the St. John Napomik
Roman Catholic Church at 66th Street.
October 22, 1939
